     <meta name="title" its:translate="yes">GPU Pass-Through for NVIDIA Cards</meta>
     <meta name="social-descr" its:translate="yes">Assign an NVIDIA GPU to a virtual machine for high-performance computing</meta>

     <!-- Search -->
     <meta name="description" its:translate="yes">Configure NVIDIA GPU pass-through to assign a physical GPU to a virtual machine for compute-intensive workloads</meta>

       <abstract>
         <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
             <term>WHAT?</term>
             <listitem>
               <para>
                 GPU pass-through allows you to assign a physical NVIDIA GPU directly to a virtual machine, providing near-native graphics and compute performance.
               </para>
             </listitem>
           </varlistentry>
           <varlistentry>
             <term>WHY?</term>
             <listitem>
               <para>
                 Use GPU pass-through for machine learning, AI workloads, 3D rendering, and other compute-intensive tasks that require direct hardware access.
               </para>
             </listitem>
           </varlistentry>
           <varlistentry>
             <term>EFFORT</term>
             <listitem>
               <para>
                 It takes approximately 30 minutes to configure GPU pass-through and requires basic knowledge of Linux system administration, PCI devices, and virtualization.
               </para>
             </listitem>
           </varlistentry>
           <varlistentry>
             <term>GOAL</term>
             <listitem>
               <para>
                 By the end of this guide, you will have an NVIDIA GPU assigned to a virtual machine and the guest driver installed for compute workloads.
               </para>
             </listitem>
           </varlistentry>
         </variablelist>
       </abstract>
